eThekwini mayor Mxolisi Kaunda will meet business on Friday to discuss the  loss of  hundreds of millions of rand  after the devastating floods that hit  KwaZulu-Natal last week. Kaunda’s office said he would meet affected stakeholders to  plan a way to restore services and bulk infrastructure. “eThekwini has been one of the hardest hit districts with  111 wards affected and  more than 400 lives lost. The floods have adversely impacted businesses. “The loss to the eThekwini GDP  by April 14  is estimated at R737m ,  excluding the replacement value of  property  worth billions of rand”. Municipal teams are  assessing the extent of the damage to  affected businesses. TimesLIVE